1
00:00:15,000 --> 00:00:16,750
[KENSUKE grunts]

2
00:00:18,583 --> 00:00:22,500
[KENSUKE laughs] At least
it was just my finger!

3
00:00:22,583 --> 00:00:23,750
[grunts]

4
00:00:24,541 --> 00:00:25,875
[KENSUKE]
Okay.

5
00:00:25,958 --> 00:00:29,166
If you get within a 30cm
radius of him, it's curtains.

6
00:00:29,250 --> 00:00:31,708
On that note,
please welcome Kobayashi.

7
00:00:31,791 --> 00:00:35,375
If you step within this
red line, you become red paste.

8
00:00:35,458 --> 00:00:36,333
No way.

9
00:00:36,416 --> 00:00:37,250
Uh!

10
00:00:37,333 --> 00:00:38,875
[NORO]
You're out of your mind.

11
00:00:38,958 --> 00:00:40,083
[KENSUKE]
Huh?

12
00:00:40,166 --> 00:00:42,250
How could you invite
someone so dangerous?

13
00:00:42,333 --> 00:00:44,083
It's not that bad!

14
00:00:44,166 --> 00:00:46,791
As long as you keep your
distance, there's no problem!

15
00:00:46,875 --> 00:00:48,083
[YOSHIO grunts]

16
00:00:48,166 --> 00:00:49,250
[KENSUKE gasps]

17
00:00:50,458 --> 00:00:52,583
[AKECHI gasps]

18
00:00:53,916 --> 00:00:54,958
[YOSHIO grunts]

19
00:00:55,041 --> 00:00:56,208
[AKECHI grunts]

20
00:01:00,125 --> 00:01:01,291
Uh. Sorry.

21
00:01:01,375 --> 00:01:03,750
Don't worry 'bout it.

22
00:01:03,833 --> 00:01:05,291
This is my house.

23
00:01:05,375 --> 00:01:07,291
You stay here,
you follow my rules.

24
00:01:07,375 --> 00:01:10,125
First, your life is
your responsibility.

25
00:01:10,208 --> 00:01:11,541
Hold on, boss.

26
00:01:11,625 --> 00:01:14,791
Second, don't ever call me
silly titles, like "Boss".

27
00:01:14,875 --> 00:01:17,250
Third, don't let
emotions rule you.

28
00:01:17,333 --> 00:01:19,208
Fourth, don't disobey me.

29
00:01:19,291 --> 00:01:22,041
And last, I'm the law.
End of story.

30
00:01:22,125 --> 00:01:25,916
So, can you handle that?

31
00:01:26,000 --> 00:01:27,500
Sure.

32
00:01:27,583 --> 00:01:29,625
[AKECHI] Hey, we've got
a guest. Perfect timing.

33
00:01:29,708 --> 00:01:31,875
[YOSHIO gasps]

34
00:01:31,958 --> 00:01:34,791
Go. Give it all ya got, kid.

35
00:01:34,875 --> 00:01:36,166
[YOSHIO]
Huh?

36
00:01:36,250 --> 00:01:37,583
Huh?!

37
00:01:38,583 --> 00:01:43,541
♪

38
00:03:09,208 --> 00:03:11,375
[JUNKO]
I'm sorry.

39
00:03:11,458 --> 00:03:14,125
It's the only recent
photo I have of him.

40
00:03:14,208 --> 00:03:15,833
[INOUE] Has your son
been missing long?

41
00:03:15,916 --> 00:03:18,833
[JUNKO] About three days.
He goes out often.

42
00:03:18,916 --> 00:03:20,375
But, even if he's gone all day,

43
00:03:20,458 --> 00:03:22,416
he always makes it
home in time for dinner.

44
00:03:22,500 --> 00:03:23,208
[KENSUKE]
Hey, Granny.

45
00:03:23,291 --> 00:03:23,708
[gasps]

46
00:03:23,791 --> 00:03:24,583
Hush!

47
00:03:24,666 --> 00:03:26,458
Did you ask the cops?

48
00:03:26,541 --> 00:03:27,708
Well, no.

49
00:03:27,791 --> 00:03:30,166
[KENSUKE] What made you
decide to come to us?

50
00:03:30,250 --> 00:03:31,416
[INOUE sighs]

51
00:03:31,500 --> 00:03:33,291
[NORO] Earth to jerk-face,
you're being rude!

52
00:03:33,375 --> 00:03:35,916
Well, shouldn't you always
try the cops, first?

53
00:03:36,000 --> 00:03:38,208
I'm looking after
my sick husband,

54
00:03:38,291 --> 00:03:41,166
so I can't be tied
down for long periods.

55
00:03:41,250 --> 00:03:45,375
Also, my son is somewhat
well-known these days,

56
00:03:45,458 --> 00:03:47,625
at least to sports fans.

57
00:03:47,708 --> 00:03:50,125
Wait. The Nemoto?

58
00:03:50,208 --> 00:03:52,166
Didn't he get eighth
place in kayaking?

59
00:03:52,250 --> 00:03:53,166
It was Sixth.

60
00:03:53,250 --> 00:03:55,166
[INOUE, KENSUKE]
Mm?

61
00:03:55,250 --> 00:03:57,833
[INOUE] Have you talked to any
of his co-workers or friends?

62
00:03:57,916 --> 00:04:00,958
[JUNKO] Actually, Nemoto spends
most of his time at home.

63
00:04:01,041 --> 00:04:02,208
[KENSUKE]
So, he's jobless?

64
00:04:02,291 --> 00:04:03,583
[INOUE]
Hanasaki!

65
00:04:03,666 --> 00:04:05,708
He is, I'm ashamed to say.

66
00:04:05,791 --> 00:04:07,500
Should we really look for him?

67
00:04:07,583 --> 00:04:09,916
Maybe he's trying
to be independent.

68
00:04:10,000 --> 00:04:11,500
[AKECHI gasps]

69
00:04:11,583 --> 00:04:14,708
[JUNKO] He may be a useless son,
but now that his father is ill,

70
00:04:14,791 --> 00:04:18,208
if anything were to happen to
him, I don't know what I'd do.

71
00:04:18,291 --> 00:04:19,500
[YOSHIO]
Then...

72
00:04:19,583 --> 00:04:20,833
...just kill yourself.

73
00:04:20,916 --> 00:04:22,583
[ALL gasp]

74
00:04:22,666 --> 00:04:25,708
If you're suffering,
then why not?

75
00:04:25,791 --> 00:04:28,333
It's not like there's
anything's stopping you.

76
00:04:29,541 --> 00:04:32,041
[INOUE] Do not speak to Nao.
Don't even look at her.

77
00:04:32,125 --> 00:04:36,833
I won't tolerate rudeness from
either one of you. Am I clear?

78
00:04:36,916 --> 00:04:38,750
I didn't say anything wrong.

79
00:04:38,833 --> 00:04:41,000
He's still a newbie,
cut him some slack.

80
00:04:41,083 --> 00:04:43,625
"New" has nothing to do with it.

81
00:04:43,708 --> 00:04:44,458
[grunts]

82
00:04:44,541 --> 00:04:46,625
Come on, let's see a smile.

83
00:04:46,708 --> 00:04:47,708
I'm totally against this.

84
00:04:47,791 --> 00:04:48,833
[NORO]
That makes two of us.

85
00:04:48,916 --> 00:04:49,666
[YOSHIO]
Hmph.

86
00:04:49,750 --> 00:04:50,583
[knocking]

87
00:04:50,666 --> 00:04:52,458
[INOUE gasps]

88
00:04:52,541 --> 00:04:54,125
[children chatter]

89
00:04:54,208 --> 00:04:55,916
[MIYANASHI] Here's the
missing person's report

90
00:04:56,000 --> 00:04:59,416
and related documents.
All analog media, as requested.

91
00:04:59,500 --> 00:05:01,416
[INOUE] You got these
together pretty fast.

92
00:05:01,500 --> 00:05:03,166
Yeah, Nao just
happened to have 'em.

93
00:05:03,250 --> 00:05:04,666
Not another word, Miya.

94
00:05:04,750 --> 00:05:06,791
Aren't you at the end
of your rope on this?

95
00:05:06,875 --> 00:05:09,416
Keep talking, and you're
handling the commission fee.

96
00:05:09,500 --> 00:05:13,041
Come on. We're just talking,
there's no fee yet.

97
00:05:13,125 --> 00:05:15,625
[sighs]

98
00:05:15,708 --> 00:05:17,500
[NAKAMURA] One of our top
notch medical examiners

99
00:05:17,583 --> 00:05:19,625
just pulled a disappearing act.

100
00:05:19,708 --> 00:05:22,583
[INOUE] I see. We've both
got a missing persons' case.

101
00:05:22,666 --> 00:05:25,208
All the higher-ups told us
to leave it alone, but--

102
00:05:25,291 --> 00:05:26,333
I swear to God.

103
00:05:26,416 --> 00:05:28,166
So how 'bout a little
give-and-take?

104
00:05:28,250 --> 00:05:30,333
Our information
for some of yours?

105
00:05:30,416 --> 00:05:33,166
He's nice. Unlike some people.

106
00:05:33,250 --> 00:05:35,583
[INOUE] You're being
rude again, Hanasaki.

107
00:05:35,666 --> 00:05:37,791
[NAKAMURA] Missing or not,
he wasn't the sort of man

108
00:05:37,875 --> 00:05:40,791
who would abandon his
work out of the blue.

109
00:05:40,875 --> 00:05:42,333
So what's your name, newbie?

110
00:05:42,416 --> 00:05:43,250
[YOSHIO]
Hm?

111
00:05:43,333 --> 00:05:44,875
[KENSUKE]
This is Kobayashi.

112
00:05:44,958 --> 00:05:48,750
[NAKAMURA] Ah! Another cute
face for the boys' club, huh?

113
00:05:48,833 --> 00:05:51,541
My! Akechi sure knows
how to pick'em.

114
00:05:51,625 --> 00:05:52,375
[YOSHIO]
Uh...

115
00:05:52,458 --> 00:05:53,750
If you had a face like that,

116
00:05:53,833 --> 00:05:55,333
I wouldn't mind
having you around.

117
00:05:55,416 --> 00:05:58,291
There's more to a man
than just his face.

118
00:05:58,375 --> 00:06:02,625
[CHILDREN chatter, giggle]

119
00:06:02,708 --> 00:06:04,625
[gasps, grunts]

120
00:06:04,708 --> 00:06:07,125
--[NAKAMURA gasps]
--[MIYANASHI] Hm?

121
00:06:07,208 --> 00:06:09,291
Well, see ya later!

122
00:06:11,083 --> 00:06:12,416
[NAKAMURA exhales]

123
00:06:15,250 --> 00:06:18,875
[KENSUKE grunts]
That was close.

124
00:06:18,958 --> 00:06:21,000
[NORO] I cross-referenced
Nemo's lifestyle patterns

125
00:06:21,083 --> 00:06:22,541
from just before
his disappearance,

126
00:06:22,625 --> 00:06:24,833
using his credit card activity.

127
00:06:24,916 --> 00:06:27,125
Convenience stores,
a net café, the park...

128
00:06:27,208 --> 00:06:29,458
Looks like he never went
more than 500 meters away

129
00:06:29,541 --> 00:06:31,166
from his home.

130
00:06:31,250 --> 00:06:34,208
No interactions with any
friends in his recent history.

131
00:06:34,291 --> 00:06:36,958
All his phone calls have been
with his mom or dad, too.

132
00:06:37,041 --> 00:06:38,958
A security camera caught
some footage of him,

133
00:06:39,041 --> 00:06:41,958
but nothing that will be
much help to us, sadly.

134
00:06:44,625 --> 00:06:45,791
[gasps]

135
00:06:50,083 --> 00:06:52,166
[footsteps]

136
00:06:52,250 --> 00:06:52,916
[gasps]

137
00:06:53,000 --> 00:06:54,375
What's up?

138
00:06:56,500 --> 00:06:59,083
There's too many people.
I can't walk through.

139
00:06:59,166 --> 00:07:00,333
[gasps]

140
00:07:00,416 --> 00:07:03,041
[YOSHIO] Not unless you
want to make a scene.

141
00:07:03,125 --> 00:07:06,541
Good point.
Okay, wait here a sec.

142
00:07:12,166 --> 00:07:14,416
[INOUE]
Hm...

143
00:07:14,500 --> 00:07:16,000
Did ya miss us?

144
00:07:16,083 --> 00:07:18,875
I asked all over the place,
but no one's seen the guy.

145
00:07:18,958 --> 00:07:20,166
[YOSHIO gasps]

146
00:07:21,291 --> 00:07:22,708
[INOUE gasps]

147
00:07:22,791 --> 00:07:25,375
[KENSUKE chuckles]
Wow. Graceful... Uh-oh.

148
00:07:25,458 --> 00:07:26,833
Tell me, Hanasaki.

149
00:07:26,916 --> 00:07:29,583
Is there anything useful
he brings to the team?

150
00:07:29,666 --> 00:07:31,208
Yeah. He's invincible?

151
00:07:31,291 --> 00:07:33,833
And just how is that supposed
to help us, exactly?

152
00:07:33,916 --> 00:07:35,291
All I see, so far, are demerits!

153
00:07:35,375 --> 00:07:38,083
[YOSHIO]
Dammit. It isn't my fault.

154
00:07:38,166 --> 00:07:40,541
I didn't ask for any of this.

155
00:07:40,625 --> 00:07:42,000
Kobayashi?

156
00:07:42,083 --> 00:07:44,208
I told you to leave me alone!

157
00:07:44,291 --> 00:07:45,458
[KENSUKE gasps]

158
00:07:47,666 --> 00:07:50,000
I'll go get him.

159
00:07:50,083 --> 00:07:53,541
[grunts]
Am I wrong, here?

160
00:07:55,750 --> 00:07:56,833
[gasps]

161
00:07:59,125 --> 00:08:01,041
Alleys, rooftops, and bridges.

162
00:08:01,125 --> 00:08:02,458
So predictable.

163
00:08:02,541 --> 00:08:05,541
If you want to escape,
you should change your patterns.

164
00:08:05,625 --> 00:08:06,833
[YOSHIO grunts]

165
00:08:06,916 --> 00:08:08,333
Ha, ha. Just kidding!

166
00:08:08,416 --> 00:08:10,500
I found you because
you're wearing that.

167
00:08:11,916 --> 00:08:13,375
[KENSUKE]
It's got a GPS tracker.

168
00:08:13,458 --> 00:08:15,250
Finding you was easy.

169
00:08:19,708 --> 00:08:20,458
[YOSHIO grunts]

170
00:08:20,541 --> 00:08:21,541
[KENSUKE gasps]

171
00:08:21,625 --> 00:08:23,625
[YOSHIO grunts]
Just stay away from me.

172
00:08:24,833 --> 00:08:26,208
You wanna die, right?

173
00:08:26,291 --> 00:08:27,416
[gasps]

174
00:08:27,500 --> 00:08:29,625
[KENSUKE] Then at least
leave the lock open!

175
00:08:29,708 --> 00:08:30,583
[YOSHIO]
Lock?

176
00:08:30,666 --> 00:08:31,958
Right here.

177
00:08:32,041 --> 00:08:33,125
[YOSHIO]
Uh...

178
00:08:33,208 --> 00:08:34,583
[KENSUKE]
If you keep yourself closed off,

179
00:08:34,666 --> 00:08:36,708
then all the effort I put
in doesn't mean jack squat.

180
00:08:36,791 --> 00:08:38,333
I'm not asking
you to compromise,

181
00:08:38,416 --> 00:08:40,416
just leave me an opening!

182
00:08:40,500 --> 00:08:42,791
Do you understand what
I'm trying to say here?

183
00:08:42,875 --> 00:08:45,041
Crack the window to your heart.

184
00:08:45,125 --> 00:08:50,125
[chuckling]

185
00:08:52,166 --> 00:08:55,083
[KENSUKE] What the hell?
"Window to your heart"?

186
00:08:55,166 --> 00:08:56,333
That's so corny!

187
00:08:56,416 --> 00:08:57,875
[YOSHIO]
I didn't say it.

188
00:08:57,958 --> 00:08:59,333
[KENSUKE]
Well, anyway...

189
00:08:59,416 --> 00:09:02,500
I promised I'd find a way
to kill you, and I meant it.

190
00:09:02,583 --> 00:09:06,416
Just be patient, alright?
Help us out until then.

191
00:09:06,500 --> 00:09:07,208
[YOSHIO]
But he...

192
00:09:07,291 --> 00:09:08,416
[KENSUKE]
What? Inoue?

193
00:09:08,500 --> 00:09:09,750
Don't take it personally.

194
00:09:09,833 --> 00:09:12,083
He doesn't work well with
anyone younger than him.

195
00:09:12,166 --> 00:09:15,500
He seems like he's in charge,
but he's actually the baby.

196
00:09:15,583 --> 00:09:18,666
Hm! It's really gonna bug
me to leave things like this,

197
00:09:18,750 --> 00:09:22,125
So how 'bout you and
I throw him for a loop?

198
00:09:22,208 --> 00:09:24,000
[gasps]

199
00:09:24,083 --> 00:09:27,083
I don't care.
Do whatever you like.

200
00:09:27,166 --> 00:09:28,000
[laughs]

201
00:09:28,083 --> 00:09:29,666
[MAN A]
Be quiet, damn brats!

202
00:09:29,750 --> 00:09:30,958
[KENSUKE]
Uh?

203
00:09:31,041 --> 00:09:33,083
[MAN A grunts]
Get that outta my face!

204
00:09:33,166 --> 00:09:35,083
Oops! Sorry 'bout that.

205
00:09:35,166 --> 00:09:37,333
[MAN B] If you're sorry,
then turn it off already!

206
00:09:37,416 --> 00:09:40,708
Hey, perfect timing.
Have you seen this man?

207
00:09:40,791 --> 00:09:41,625
He disappeared rec--

208
00:09:41,708 --> 00:09:43,083
[MAN 3A]
Don't know, don't care.

209
00:09:43,166 --> 00:09:44,500
Look, we're just
trying to find him.

210
00:09:44,583 --> 00:09:45,875
[MAN A]
Put a sock in it!

211
00:09:45,958 --> 00:09:47,958
Okay, then do you know where
some more helpful bums

212
00:09:48,041 --> 00:09:48,833
might be camping out?

213
00:09:48,916 --> 00:09:51,333
[MAN B]
Screw yourself!

214
00:09:51,416 --> 00:09:52,833
Let's go.

215
00:09:54,500 --> 00:09:55,666
[KENSUKE]
Uh.

216
00:09:55,750 --> 00:09:58,291
[MAN C chuckles]
This group'll take anyone in.

217
00:09:58,375 --> 00:09:59,875
If they pass a physical.

218
00:09:59,958 --> 00:10:00,708
Per...

219
00:10:00,791 --> 00:10:03,333
Thanks for the tip, mister!

220
00:10:03,416 --> 00:10:04,916
[YOSHIO, KENSUKE]
Hm?

221
00:10:05,000 --> 00:10:07,333
How about a tip
for me, little man?

222
00:10:07,416 --> 00:10:09,541
[YOSHIO gasps]

223
00:10:13,958 --> 00:10:16,541
[FEMALE VOICE] At Persephone,
we offer on-going support

224
00:10:16,625 --> 00:10:18,500
for the hopeless
in their old age.

225
00:10:18,583 --> 00:10:21,458
Cast off your loneliness,
and leave fear behind.

226
00:10:21,541 --> 00:10:22,916
Our facilities--

227
00:10:23,000 --> 00:10:25,250
[NORO] Sounds like a super
shady group, if you ask me.

228
00:10:25,333 --> 00:10:27,166
But, I guess if you're
the target audience,

229
00:10:27,250 --> 00:10:29,041
it probably sounds
like paradise.

230
00:10:29,125 --> 00:10:30,666
[NORO]
To put it in terms that someone

231
00:10:30,750 --> 00:10:32,791
with the intellect
of a sea slug, like you,

232
00:10:32,875 --> 00:10:35,875
can understand, they protect
the dignity of the hopeless.

233
00:10:35,958 --> 00:10:37,583
They even get free
food and shelter.

234
00:10:37,666 --> 00:10:39,083
[KENSUKE]
Mm-hm! I totally get it.

235
00:10:39,166 --> 00:10:41,583
[NORO]
You don't, but whatever.

236
00:10:41,666 --> 00:10:43,583
We just need to know
if our target is here.

237
00:10:43,666 --> 00:10:45,125
Anything else is a distraction.

238
00:10:45,208 --> 00:10:47,875
Aren't you gonna thank
Kobayashi for getting this info?

239
00:10:47,958 --> 00:10:49,375
Wasn't planning on it.

240
00:10:49,458 --> 00:10:53,541
He's been pretty useful.
He deserves some credit.

241
00:10:53,625 --> 00:10:55,625
Answers come first.

242
00:10:55,708 --> 00:10:56,791
Aw, come on!

243
00:10:56,875 --> 00:10:59,125
Enough. Don't try to meddle.

244
00:10:59,208 --> 00:11:01,416
You're cool with that?

245
00:11:01,500 --> 00:11:02,916
[FRONT DESK WOMAN]
I'm sorry, sir.

246
00:11:03,000 --> 00:11:04,583
We can't allow visitors if
the resident they're visiting

247
00:11:04,666 --> 00:11:06,166
hasn't given prior consent.

248
00:11:06,250 --> 00:11:08,416
[INOUE] Can you at least
tell us if Kouichi Nemoto

249
00:11:08,500 --> 00:11:09,791
is staying here?

250
00:11:09,875 --> 00:11:11,291
[FRONT DESK WOMAN 3A]
Policy forbids me to answer

251
00:11:11,375 --> 00:11:14,125
such questions in order to
protect our resident's privacy.

252
00:11:14,208 --> 00:11:17,000
Come on, lady, give us
something to work with here.

253
00:11:17,083 --> 00:11:18,500
I'm very sorry, sir.

254
00:11:18,583 --> 00:11:21,125
You really can't,
no matter what?

255
00:11:21,208 --> 00:11:23,166
Don't make me call security.

256
00:11:23,250 --> 00:11:24,666
I'll build in a
shrine in your honor!

257
00:11:24,750 --> 00:11:27,333
Please, just throw
me a freakin' bone!

258
00:11:31,166 --> 00:11:33,291
Well, that didn't work.

259
00:11:33,375 --> 00:11:35,375
You're up.
Smash through the wall!

260
00:11:35,458 --> 00:11:36,500
Huh?

261
00:11:36,583 --> 00:11:38,750
Just walk up to it,
and Ka-boom! Cool?

262
00:11:38,833 --> 00:11:40,083
That won't be necessary.

263
00:11:40,166 --> 00:11:41,166
[YOSHIO, KENSUKE]
Hm?

264
00:11:41,250 --> 00:11:42,458
You got a better plan?

265
00:11:42,541 --> 00:11:44,333
You can climb, can't you?

266
00:11:48,250 --> 00:11:49,666
[KENSUKE chuckles]

267
00:11:53,458 --> 00:11:54,375
What's my time?

268
00:11:54,458 --> 00:11:55,625
[NORO]
Forty-two seconds.

269
00:11:55,708 --> 00:11:57,875
I guess that's about right.

270
00:12:00,875 --> 00:12:03,791
[YOSHIO grunts]

271
00:12:03,875 --> 00:12:05,875
[laughs]

272
00:12:05,958 --> 00:12:07,958
[NORO]
How incompetent can you get?

273
00:12:08,041 --> 00:12:08,916
[KENSUKE]
No kidding.

274
00:12:09,000 --> 00:12:11,000
[NORO]
It's no laughing matter.

275
00:12:11,083 --> 00:12:14,125
[YOSHIO grunts, pants]

276
00:12:14,208 --> 00:12:17,041
Right. Let's get going.

277
00:12:17,125 --> 00:12:18,375
[YOSHIO]
Hm.

278
00:12:19,916 --> 00:12:21,333
[KENSUKE]
Knock, knock.

279
00:12:26,083 --> 00:12:27,041
[KENSUKE]
Huh?

280
00:12:29,291 --> 00:12:31,041
[INOUE]
Still waiting on the layout.

281
00:12:31,125 --> 00:12:32,500
Keep your shirt on.

282
00:12:32,583 --> 00:12:33,041
[KENSUKE whistles]

283
00:12:33,125 --> 00:12:34,500
[PIPPO hoots]

284
00:12:36,500 --> 00:12:37,666
[KENSUKE]
A net café?

285
00:12:37,750 --> 00:12:38,916
[YOSHIO]
More like a barn.

286
00:12:39,000 --> 00:12:40,291
[NORO]
I'll use facial recognition

287
00:12:40,375 --> 00:12:43,125
to see if Nemo's in there.

288
00:12:43,208 --> 00:12:43,916
Was that?

289
00:12:44,000 --> 00:12:45,291
[KENSUKE]
Huh?

290
00:12:45,375 --> 00:12:47,500
Those are the missing people
from Nakamura's files.

291
00:12:47,583 --> 00:12:49,250
I'm sure of it.

292
00:12:49,333 --> 00:12:50,250
Really?

293
00:12:50,333 --> 00:12:51,583
[YOSHIO grunts]

294
00:12:51,666 --> 00:12:53,875
None of them have had work
for at least ten years.

295
00:12:53,958 --> 00:12:56,250
They've been living by
leeching off their parents.

296
00:12:56,333 --> 00:12:59,208
In millennial terms,
they're textbook <i>NEETs</i> .

297
00:12:59,291 --> 00:13:01,083
[NORO]
As far as I can tell,

298
00:13:01,166 --> 00:13:03,750
every one of them is a deadbeat,
through and through.

299
00:13:03,833 --> 00:13:05,416
And all of their parents
are either dead,

300
00:13:05,500 --> 00:13:07,625
in hospice, or a nursing home.

301
00:13:07,708 --> 00:13:10,333
Sounds like they'd get
along with kayak guy.

302
00:13:10,416 --> 00:13:12,166
[INOUE] There'd be no
end to it if the police tried

303
00:13:12,250 --> 00:13:14,250
to investigate
every one of them.

304
00:13:14,333 --> 00:13:15,333
[KENSUKE gasps]

305
00:13:16,708 --> 00:13:18,958
[INOUE]
What now?

306
00:13:19,041 --> 00:13:20,750
I didn't do anything. The wall--

307
00:13:20,833 --> 00:13:23,375
Nothing to worry about.
I just tripped.

308
00:13:23,458 --> 00:13:26,708
We'll let you know if
we find him, okay?

309
00:13:26,791 --> 00:13:27,458
Sup, old man?

310
00:13:27,541 --> 00:13:29,208
What the-- Hey!

311
00:13:29,291 --> 00:13:32,833
So why are you in this place?
Is it against your will?

312
00:13:32,916 --> 00:13:35,875
Security! What's goin' on?
There's a kid in here!

313
00:13:35,958 --> 00:13:37,375
[KENSUKE]
Huh?

314
00:13:37,458 --> 00:13:39,416
[MAN 3D] This is my room,
you little brat! Get out! Now!

315
00:13:39,500 --> 00:13:40,500
--[alarm buzzes]
--[YOSHIO] Move it!

316
00:13:40,583 --> 00:13:41,875
--[alarm buzzes]
--[KENSUKE grunts] Crap!

317
00:13:41,958 --> 00:13:47,041
[SECURITY GUARDS shouting]

318
00:13:47,125 --> 00:13:49,208
[KENSUKE]
Yikes.

319
00:13:49,291 --> 00:13:50,500
So what do we do?

320
00:13:50,583 --> 00:13:51,916
You're getting into this,
aren't you?

321
00:13:52,000 --> 00:13:53,833
You wanna take 'em out?

322
00:13:53,916 --> 00:13:55,458
You know I don't want that.

323
00:13:55,541 --> 00:13:58,375
[KENSUKE] Then we'll have to
find some way around them.

324
00:13:58,458 --> 00:13:59,250
[OLD MAN A]
Get in.

325
00:13:59,333 --> 00:14:00,416
Huh?

326
00:14:00,958 --> 00:14:05,833
[SECURITY OFFICERS chatter]

327
00:14:05,916 --> 00:14:07,083
Thanks for the save.

328
00:14:07,166 --> 00:14:09,125
This place wasn't meant
to be a playground.

329
00:14:09,208 --> 00:14:10,583
You kids should just run home.

330
00:14:10,666 --> 00:14:12,208
Sure. We'll do that.

331
00:14:12,291 --> 00:14:16,125
Right after we find this guy.
Does he look familiar?

332
00:14:16,208 --> 00:14:17,583
[OLD MAN A]
When did he disappear?

333
00:14:17,666 --> 00:14:20,583
[KENSUKE] Uh...
Something like three days ago?

334
00:14:20,666 --> 00:14:23,083
[OLD MAN A] Then he'd still
be going through the tests.

335
00:14:23,166 --> 00:14:24,458
[KENSUKE]
Tests?

336
00:14:24,541 --> 00:14:26,833
[OLD MAN 3A] Applicants have
to pass a physical exam

337
00:14:26,916 --> 00:14:30,625
and an acceptance test to know
whether they'll fit in here.

338
00:14:30,708 --> 00:14:32,500
Check the floor below us.

339
00:14:32,583 --> 00:14:34,958
Heh! Thank you.

340
00:14:35,041 --> 00:14:38,333
Hey. Why are you here, anyway?

341
00:14:38,416 --> 00:14:40,291
[OLD MAN A]
It's comfortable here.

342
00:14:40,375 --> 00:14:42,875
I don't have to look
anyone in the face.

343
00:14:44,541 --> 00:14:45,833
[OLD MAN A]
If I die,

344
00:14:45,916 --> 00:14:48,916
they'll take care of my body
without telling anyone.

345
00:14:51,208 --> 00:14:54,625
I think I understand why
it appealed to you.

346
00:14:54,708 --> 00:14:57,541
[YOSHIO]
Tsk. I don't understand them.

347
00:14:57,625 --> 00:15:00,041
Why would these people
be so determined to live,

348
00:15:00,125 --> 00:15:01,791
they'd stay in this place?

349
00:15:01,875 --> 00:15:03,208
[KENSUKE]
Huh?

350
00:15:03,291 --> 00:15:05,500
They might as well die.
Make it easy on themselves.

351
00:15:06,916 --> 00:15:09,208
But dying is scary.
And besides--

352
00:15:09,291 --> 00:15:10,750
[gasps]

353
00:15:10,833 --> 00:15:13,166
You don't know if dying will
solve anything. How could you?

354
00:15:13,250 --> 00:15:14,291
[gasps]

355
00:15:14,375 --> 00:15:15,916
[KENSUKE chuckles]
Don't get mad, dude.

356
00:15:16,000 --> 00:15:16,708
You know I'm right.

357
00:15:16,791 --> 00:15:17,625
[OLD MAN A grunts]

358
00:15:17,708 --> 00:15:18,458
[YOSHIO]
Look!

359
00:15:18,541 --> 00:15:19,541
[KENSUKE]
Hm?

360
00:15:19,625 --> 00:15:21,958
[OLD MAN A grunts]
Stop.

361
00:15:22,041 --> 00:15:26,583
[grunting continues]

362
00:15:27,291 --> 00:15:28,625
[KENSUKE]
Old man!

363
00:15:28,708 --> 00:15:30,833
[LAB MAN A]
Type B-positive en route.

364
00:15:34,916 --> 00:15:37,500
[KENSUKE, YOSHIO gasp]

365
00:15:37,583 --> 00:15:38,708
[INOUE]
Hm?

366
00:15:38,791 --> 00:15:39,875
[KENSUKE] Something's wrong
with this place.

367
00:15:39,958 --> 00:15:42,333
One of the geezers
was just carted off.

368
00:15:42,416 --> 00:15:44,083
[INOUE]
Did you forget the mission?

369
00:15:44,166 --> 00:15:45,375
Huh?

370
00:15:45,458 --> 00:15:48,041
[INOUE] Our priority is
finding Kouichi Nemoto!

371
00:15:48,125 --> 00:15:51,291
[grunts]
To hell with that!

372
00:15:51,375 --> 00:15:53,250
He's gone rogue again.

373
00:15:53,333 --> 00:15:55,500
[INOUE] His call.
Let him deal with it.

374
00:15:55,583 --> 00:15:58,083
Right. I'll do that.

375
00:15:58,166 --> 00:16:03,125
[KENSUKE, YOSHIO pant, grunt]

376
00:16:08,250 --> 00:16:09,250
[KENSUKE]
Grab on!

377
00:16:09,333 --> 00:16:10,500
[YOSHIO grunts]

378
00:16:10,583 --> 00:16:14,166
[KENSUKE grunts]

379
00:16:16,875 --> 00:16:17,791
So many.

380
00:16:17,875 --> 00:16:19,958
Tsk.

381
00:16:20,041 --> 00:16:21,208
[BOTH gasp]

382
00:16:23,541 --> 00:16:24,791
[BOTH gasp]

383
00:16:36,791 --> 00:16:38,791
[KENSUKE]
The hell is all this?

384
00:16:38,875 --> 00:16:40,041
[KENSUKE grunts]

385
00:16:41,375 --> 00:16:42,916
Let him go!

386
00:16:44,458 --> 00:16:45,375
[SECURITY OFFICER A]
Stop!

387
00:16:45,458 --> 00:16:47,375
[SECURITY OFFICER B]
Don't move!

388
00:16:47,458 --> 00:16:48,500
[KYOUMOTO]
Sorry about that.

389
00:16:48,583 --> 00:16:50,750
[YOSHIO, KENSUKE gasps]

390
00:16:50,833 --> 00:16:52,125
[KYOUMOTO]
If you'd gotten any closer,

391
00:16:52,208 --> 00:16:55,916
your bacteria could ruin
these perfectly good organs.

392
00:16:56,000 --> 00:16:58,916
That's what you were
planning to do with him?

393
00:16:59,000 --> 00:17:00,708
[KYOUMOTO] All of our
residents will help us save

394
00:17:00,791 --> 00:17:02,041
countless lives.

395
00:17:02,125 --> 00:17:04,125
Compared to spending their
last years in idleness

396
00:17:04,208 --> 00:17:08,500
and shame, this is a far
better use of their bodies.

397
00:17:08,583 --> 00:17:09,166
[KYOUMOTO]
Now, why don't you boys
forget about what you saw
and just run on home?

398
00:17:09,250 --> 00:17:09,708
[INOUE]
Kobayashi.

399
00:17:09,791 --> 00:17:11,666
[gasps]

400
00:17:11,750 --> 00:17:12,541
Huh?

401
00:17:12,625 --> 00:17:13,833
[INOUE]
Let me see his face.

402
00:17:13,916 --> 00:17:15,458
Tell Kensuke.

403
00:17:15,541 --> 00:17:16,458
[INOUE]
Just do it.

404
00:17:16,541 --> 00:17:18,458
Like this?

405
00:17:18,541 --> 00:17:19,958
It's him!

406
00:17:20,041 --> 00:17:22,333
The medical examiner Inspector
Nakamura was looking for!

407
00:17:22,416 --> 00:17:23,833
[NORO]
No way!

408
00:17:23,916 --> 00:17:27,125
[KYOUMOTO] All vermin are
looking for a good place to die.

409
00:17:27,208 --> 00:17:29,416
I'm simply helping them
to find that place.

410
00:17:29,500 --> 00:17:31,666
We have the same interests.

411
00:17:31,750 --> 00:17:33,916
I told you these people
wanted to end it all.

412
00:17:34,000 --> 00:17:36,875
[NORO] God, you're dumb.
The kind of people who'd stay

413
00:17:36,958 --> 00:17:40,416
in this place don't have the
guts to live, let alone die.

414
00:17:40,500 --> 00:17:41,791
[YOSHIO gasps]
Don't call me dumb.

415
00:17:41,875 --> 00:17:43,875
[KENSUKE whistles]

416
00:17:43,958 --> 00:17:46,500
[KYOUMOTO]
Uh! What is that?

417
00:17:46,583 --> 00:17:48,666
They caught us. Now what?

418
00:17:48,750 --> 00:17:52,041
I'm glad you asked.
We cause trouble!

419
00:17:54,083 --> 00:17:55,458
[KYOUMOTO chuckles]

420
00:17:55,541 --> 00:17:56,083
[gasps]

421
00:17:56,166 --> 00:17:57,291
[KENSUKE chuckles]

422
00:18:01,041 --> 00:18:02,833
[PIPPO hoots]

423
00:18:02,916 --> 00:18:05,583
[NORO]
Hey, Koba! Heads up!

424
00:18:05,666 --> 00:18:07,250
Uh, Koba?

425
00:18:08,708 --> 00:18:10,666
[MAN E]
Huh? What's this?

426
00:18:10,750 --> 00:18:11,666
[yells]

427
00:18:11,750 --> 00:18:14,875
[MEN chattering]

428
00:18:14,958 --> 00:18:16,333
[NORO]
Run, boys!

429
00:18:17,958 --> 00:18:19,333
[KYOUMOTO]
Get downstairs, now!

430
00:18:19,416 --> 00:18:20,000
[SECURITY OFFICER B]
Right!

431
00:18:20,083 --> 00:18:25,416
[grunting]

432
00:18:25,500 --> 00:18:27,541
[KYOUMOTO grunts]

433
00:18:27,625 --> 00:18:28,875
Brat!

434
00:18:28,958 --> 00:18:30,666
[KENSUKE chuckles]

435
00:18:30,750 --> 00:18:32,125
[DOCTORS gasp]

436
00:18:33,625 --> 00:18:37,000
[KYOUMOTO growls]

437
00:18:37,083 --> 00:18:40,375
Put everything on lock down!
Don't let them get outside!

438
00:18:40,458 --> 00:18:41,125
[LAB MEN shout]

439
00:18:41,208 --> 00:18:42,666
[KENSUKE]
Kobayashi.

440
00:18:42,750 --> 00:18:43,958
Do your thing.

441
00:18:44,041 --> 00:18:45,125
But I don't want to.

442
00:18:45,208 --> 00:18:47,750
Unlock your freakin' window!

443
00:18:47,833 --> 00:18:48,750
[YOSHIO]
Tsk.

444
00:18:48,833 --> 00:18:50,541
[DOCTOR B pants]

445
00:18:50,625 --> 00:18:52,125
--[DOCTOR B groans]
--[LAB MEN shout]

446
00:18:52,208 --> 00:18:54,250
[YOSHIO]
That wasn't my fault, okay?

447
00:18:55,833 --> 00:18:57,250
[KYOUMOTO] Don't just
stand there, grab him!

448
00:18:57,333 --> 00:18:58,916
Make a break for it!

449
00:19:02,458 --> 00:19:04,833
The truth's out there,
no matter what you do now.

450
00:19:04,916 --> 00:19:06,416
[KYOUMOTO]
Huh?

451
00:19:06,500 --> 00:19:08,666
Our club's professional shut-in
just sent that video to every

452
00:19:08,750 --> 00:19:11,291
cop in the city.
Sucks to be you.

453
00:19:11,375 --> 00:19:12,750
[gasps]

454
00:19:12,833 --> 00:19:16,875
[police sirens blaring]

455
00:19:16,958 --> 00:19:18,625
[MEN shouting]

456
00:19:18,708 --> 00:19:21,541
[NEMOTO pants]

457
00:19:21,625 --> 00:19:22,875
Search target captured!

458
00:19:22,958 --> 00:19:24,416
Get offa me, ya gimp!

459
00:19:24,500 --> 00:19:26,500
[NEMOTO groans]

460
00:19:26,583 --> 00:19:29,958
Please, sir. Don't make this
any harder than it has to be.

461
00:19:35,333 --> 00:19:37,791
[NEMOTO grunts]
You just had to butt in.

462
00:19:37,875 --> 00:19:39,291
[JUNKO]
Please come home.

463
00:19:39,375 --> 00:19:41,541
Fine, but I'm not helpin'
you take care of the old man,

464
00:19:41,625 --> 00:19:42,583
got it?

465
00:19:42,666 --> 00:19:43,833
Jerk.

466
00:19:43,916 --> 00:19:46,583
Was this really worth
saving a guy like him?

467
00:19:46,666 --> 00:19:51,875
[KENSUKE] Mm... I don't really
think about that stuff.

468
00:19:51,958 --> 00:19:53,291
[YOSHIO grunts]

469
00:19:53,375 --> 00:19:54,916
[NAKAMURA]
It's true that Kyoumoto

470
00:19:55,000 --> 00:19:58,291
once worked for our department,
but that isn't the case anymore.

471
00:19:58,375 --> 00:20:00,500
His crimes are clear,
and I promise that he will be

472
00:20:00,583 --> 00:20:03,708
prosecuted to the
fullest extent of the law.

473
00:20:06,375 --> 00:20:07,875
Hey, keep your chin up.

474
00:20:07,958 --> 00:20:09,250
[NAKAMURA]
Stop talking.

475
00:20:09,333 --> 00:20:10,916
[MIYANASHI grunts]

476
00:20:17,541 --> 00:20:19,416
[INOUE]
Kobayashi is dangerous!

477
00:20:19,500 --> 00:20:21,250
[grunts]
Huh?

478
00:20:21,333 --> 00:20:23,625
[INOUE] His power could
injure or kill someone,

479
00:20:23,708 --> 00:20:26,041
and he doesn't even know
how to keep it under control!

480
00:20:26,125 --> 00:20:28,625
[NORO] Not to mention
he's a total freakazoid.

481
00:20:28,708 --> 00:20:30,750
[KENSUKE] Hey, you don't
have any room to talk, Noro.

482
00:20:30,833 --> 00:20:33,458
You flip out whenever
someone calls you a shut-in.

483
00:20:33,541 --> 00:20:35,750
[INOUE] It's only a matter of
time before he makes a mess

484
00:20:35,833 --> 00:20:37,416
that we won't be
able to clean up.

485
00:20:37,500 --> 00:20:39,291
[AKECHI]
Nao can take care of it.

486
00:20:39,375 --> 00:20:40,916
[INOUE]
You can't be serious!

487
00:20:41,000 --> 00:20:44,291
Powers or not, the kid's the
only one that followed my rules.

488
00:20:44,375 --> 00:20:45,625
Huh?

489
00:20:45,708 --> 00:20:47,125
[AKECHI] Hanasaki, you let
your emotions rule you

490
00:20:47,208 --> 00:20:49,666
and acted on your own instead
of sticking to the job.

491
00:20:49,750 --> 00:20:51,166
And it worked, didn't it?

492
00:20:51,250 --> 00:20:53,875
[AKECHI] Noro, whether a member
of this team lives or dies

493
00:20:53,958 --> 00:20:55,458
is their own responsibility,

494
00:20:55,541 --> 00:20:57,916
but you came running to
me for help, didn't you?

495
00:20:58,000 --> 00:20:59,208
[NORO]
Because Hanasaki's a--

496
00:20:59,291 --> 00:21:02,000
[AKECHI] Inoue. You insist
on calling me stupid

497
